text.tspan: Drivers of greenhouse gas emissions from agriculture, World
Greenhouse gas emissions from agriculture (E) are driven by the Pale factors:
– a: agricultural production per person (in kilocalories)
– l: land use intensity (hectares required to produce a kilocalorie)
– e: emissions per hectare of land
Source: Hong et al. (2021). Global and regional drivers of land-use emissions in 1961–2017. Nature.
